\/Getty Images","caption":"(Left to Right) Malcolm-Jamal Warner as Theodore 'Theo' Huxtable, Bill Cosby as Dr. Heathcliff 'Cliff' Huxtable, Keshia Knight Pulliam as Rudy Huxtable, Tempestt Bledsoe as Vanessa Huxtable on The Cosby Show.","alt":"(Left to Right) Malcolm-Jamal Warner as Theodore 'Theo' Huxtable, Bill Cosby as Dr. Heathcliff 'Cliff' Huxtable, Keshia Knight Pulliam as Rudy Huxtable, Tempestt Bledsoe as Vanessa Huxtable on The Cosby Show.","providers":[]},"id":3599978,"encoded_url":"http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3599978%2Fcosby-show-reruns-rape%2F","encoded_shortlink":"http%3A%2F%2Fwp.me%2Fp5HMd-f6wa","encoded_title":"So+What+Do+We+Do+About+The+Cosby+Show%3F","twitter_text":"So%20what%20do%20we%20do%20about%20%27The%20Cosby%20Show%27%3F","twitter_via":"TIMECulture","subjects":[null],"ads":{"neg":"false","post_title":"So What Do We Do About <i>The Cosby Show<\/i>?"},"Partner_Module":{"partner":"Select","post_title":"So What Do We Do About <i>The Cosby Show<\/i>?"},"email_title":"So%20What%20Do%20We%20Do%20About%20The%20Cosby%20Show%3F%20%7C%20TIME","email_body":"So%20What%20Do%20We%20Do%20About%20The%20Cosby%20Show%3F%0A%0AIf%20it%27s%20hard%20to%20%22separate%20the%20art%20from%20the%20artist%22%20this%20time%2C%20it%27s%20partly%20because%20the%20artist%20worked%20so%20hard%20to%20intertwine%20them.%20%0A%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3599978%2Fcosby-show-reruns-rape%2F","omniture":{"modules":"rr-outbrain|rr-partner|rr-mag|rr-ad|rr-share"},"outbrain":{"url":"http:\/\/time.com\/3599978\/cosby-show-reruns-rape\/","widget_id":"AR_6","hide":false}},{"url":"http:\/\/time.com\/3599721\/michelle-duggar-homophobia-gay-rights\/","shortlink":"http:\/\/wp.me\/p5HMd-f6s1","title":"Thank You, Duggars, Your Homophobia Is Really a Public Service","friendly_title":"Thank You, Duggars, Your Homophobia Is Really a Public Service","post_type":"post","available":true,"time_article":true,"comments_allowed":true,"short_title":"Thank You, Duggars, Your Homophobia Is Really a Public Service","contributor":true,"excerpt":"When gay marriage is passing in state after state, it\u2019s easy to forget that not everyone is on the bandwagon","format":"article","time":{"pretty":"Nov. 21, 2014","published":"2014-11-21 11:56:14","updated":"2014-11-21 16:56:14","minute":"11:56 am","short":"11\/21"},"authors":[{"id":262712319,"url":"https:\/\/time.com\/author\/brian-moylan\/","name":"Brian Moylan","bio":"<em>Brian Moylan is a writer and pop culture junkie who lives in New York. His work has appeared in Gawker, VICE, <\/em>New York<em> magazine, and a few other safe-for-work publications.<\/em>","short_bio":"Brian Moylan is a writer and pop culture junkie.","types":["contributor"],"twitter":"BrianJMoylan","twitter_url":"https:\/\/twitter.com\/BrianJMoylan","gplus":"","fb":"","email":"","thumbnail":null,"contributor":true}],"content":"<aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-outbrain\" data-name=\"rr-outbrain\"><div class=\"OUTBRAIN\" data-src=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3599721\/michelle-duggar-homophobia-gay-rights\/\" data-widget-id=\"SB_2\" data-ob-template=\"timemag\"><\/div><\/aside><p>You would think that, decades after Anita Bryant went on a crusade to rid gay people from public life, we&rsquo;d be sick of hearing D-listers call us names and voice their hatred against us in public. The latest to really take a stand against gays is Michelle Duggar, the human baby factory who is the matriarch on the reality show &ldquo;19 Kids and Counting.&rdquo; This may sound strange, but I would actually like to thank her for her recent behavior.<\/p>\n<aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-partner\" data-name=\"rr-partner\"><div class=\"read-more-list\"><h6 class=\"read-more-list-h\">More<\/h6><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3598207\/bill-cosby-rape-accusations-silence\/\" class=\"read-more-list-article\" data-event=\"rr-more\">Bill Cosby, Camille Cosby and the Oppressive Power of Silence<\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3596105\/don-lemon-bill-cosby-rape-myths\/\" class=\"read-more-list-article\" data-event=\"rr-more\">Don Lemon Didn\u2019t Just Victim-Blame&#8211;He Perpetuated Multiple Rape Myths<\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/www.nbcnews.com\/storyline\/michael-brown-shooting\/pair-suspected-trying-acquire-bombs-ferguson-protests-n254021?cid=par-time_20141122\" class=\"read-more-partner-article\" data-event=\"rr-partner\" target=\"_blank\">Feds Suspect Pair Sought Bombs for Ferguson Protests <span>NBC News<\/span><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/www.nbcnews.com\/news\/crime-courts\/ohio-men-wrongly-convicted-murder-after-39-years-released-n253356?cid=par-time_20141122\" class=\"read-more-partner-article\" data-event=\"rr-partner\" target=\"_blank\">Two Ohio Men Wrongly Convicted of Murder Walk Free <span>NBC News<\/span><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/www.nbcnews.com\/news\/us-news\/fsu-shooter-myron-may-left-message-i-do-not-want-n253436?cid=par-time_20141122\" class=\"read-more-partner-article\" data-event=\"rr-partner\" target=\"_blank\">FSU Shooter Left Message: 'I Do Not Want to Die in Vain' <span>NBC News<\/span><\/a><\/div><\/aside><p>The Duggars stirred up controversy when they recently asked for people to post pictures of <a href=\"http:\/\/www.usmagazine.com\/celebrity-news\/news\/duggars-issue-kissing-challenge-delete-pics-of-same-sex-couples-20141211\">married couples kissing<\/a> on their Facebook page and then deleted a picture of a gay married couple kissing. (Hello? Who do you think is keeping TLC in business?) When the news of this leaked, activists directed people to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.change.org\/p\/the-learning-channel-end-lgbtq-fear-mongering-by-the-duggars\">sign a Change.org petition<\/a> to &ldquo;end LGBTQ fear mongering by the Duggars&rdquo; and calls for the show to be canceled because of their behavior. It now has well over 120,000 signatures.<\/p>\n<aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-mag\" data-name=\"rr-mag\"><div class=\"read-more-inline magazine has-cover\"><h6 class=\"read-more-list-h read-more-popular\">Popular Among Subscribers<\/h6>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"popular-lead\"><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3547827\/the-art-of-science\/?pcd=pw-pas\"><img src=\"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/10\/timeinterstellarcover.jpg?w=560\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" data-loaded=\"true\"><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3547827\/the-art-of-science\/?pcd=pw-pas\" class=\"read-more-article\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title time-icons time-icons-key\"><em>Interstellar<\/em>, Where No Movie Has Gone Before<\/h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/subscription.time.com\/storefront\/subscribe-to-time\/link\/1019509.html\" class=\"subscribe-button\">Subscribe<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3547825\/nucor-tries-to-reverse-decline-in-american-steelmaking\/?pcd=pw-pas\" class=\"read-more-article\" format-article><h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title time-icons time-icons-key\">The Last Men of Steel<\/h3><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3547828\/review-interstellar-christopher-nolan\/?pcd=pw-pas\" class=\"read-more-article\" format-article><h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title time-icons time-icons-key\">Review: <em>Interstellar\u2019s<\/em> Wonder of Worlds Beyond<\/h3><\/a><\/div><\/aside><p>For what it&rsquo;s worth, this isn&rsquo;t Michelle&rsquo;s only recent offense. She also recorded a robocall asking that the people of Fayetteville, Arkansas, vote to repeal a law that stops discrimination based on gender identity. Basically she wants people to be able to discriminate against transgender men and women.<\/p>\n<p>Now some people think that we need to silence the Duggars and those like them. I think we should let them keep going. Nothing defeats complacency like knowing exactly where gay people stand with millions of Americans. Now, it&rsquo;s not a shock that the overly religious Duggars don&rsquo;t like gay people. That&rsquo;s sort of like saying that Paula Deen likes butter. But, when gay marriage is passing in state after state, it&rsquo;s easy to forget that not everyone is on the bandwagon. There are still large groups of Americans out there who want to rob us of our rights, and if we don&rsquo;t stay vigilant, we&rsquo;ll never win the war.<\/p>\n<p>Right now we&rsquo;re having a bit of success in dealing with pop culture homophobes. In May, HGTV decided to cancel a show they were planning to air featuring David and Jason Benham when <a href=\"http:\/\/www.cnn.com\/2014\/05\/08\/showbiz\/tv\/benham-brothers-hgtv\/\">it was discovered<\/a> that they had made some nasty comments about gay people very publicly.<\/p>\n<p>Phil Robertson of Duck Dynasty made some <a href=\"http:\/\/www.gq.com\/entertainment\/television\/201401\/duck-dynasty-phil-robertson\">very homophobic comments to <em>GQ<\/em><\/a> this January, and <a href=\"http:\/\/popwatch.ew.com\/2014\/05\/23\/duck-dynasty-phil-robertson-antigay-sermon-video\/\">was mouthing off once again<\/a> this May about how gay sex is unnatural. He was suspended from A&amp;E briefly for his behavior and the ratings for the show <a href=\"http:\/\/www.mediaite.com\/tv\/duck-dynasty-ratings-fall-even-further-in-second-episode-after-robertson-controversy\/\">tanked after his disclosure<\/a>.<\/p><div class=\"content-ad\" id=\"content-ad-3599721\"><\/div>\n<p>That&rsquo;s why we need these people to keep talking. There&rsquo;s no doubt in my mind that there is hatred in the hearts of many people for LGBTQ men and women in this country, but if that hatred just stays in their hearts they&rsquo;ll be working against us without our knowledge. The louder they become, the easier it is to target them. And when we can target them, well, we&rsquo;ve seen that we can do things to shut them up. If only we could give them all a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=dS91gT3XT_A\">pie in the face<\/a> like Anita Bryant got.<\/p>\n<p>Having loudmouth opponents also serves as an effective recruiting tool for allies to gay civil rights causes. Like it or not, reality stars like the Duggars and especially the Robertsons&ndash;whose most recent season finale still clocked almost <a href=\"http:\/\/www.thewrap.com\/duck-dynasty-finale-ratings-drop-from-season-5-ender\/\" target=\"_blank\">4 million viewers<\/a>&ndash;have a huge stage. When they make these sorts of remarks there is always a media firestorm and each time that happens, I would like to think that there is at least one fan out there who thinks, &ldquo;God, what an idiot.&rdquo; Hopefully that opens up some minds and shows those out there who may not be very hospitable to the &ldquo;gay lifestyle&rdquo; that bigotry is distasteful no matter how it manifests itself.<\/p>\n<p>We don&rsquo;t get to teach these lessons, show our strength or fight these battles if these people are silent. We need people like Michelle Duggar to be loud in order to get the hard work of activism done. So no matter how much it sucks, we have to just take it on the chin every time one of these yahoos has the bright idea to spout off. Trust me, it&rsquo;s for the greater good. Every time a reality star says something ignorant about the LGBT community, a gay angel gets her wings.<\/p>\n<p>Oscar Wilde, one of the world&rsquo;s most public and tragic gay men, said &ldquo;True friends stab you in the front.&rdquo; There is no doubt in my mind that there are plenty of misinformed people in America carrying daggers against gay people, including those who have a public forum to discuss those views. Why would we want them hiding that hatred in the shadows when, out in the open, it can be diffused, acted on and used as a teaching tool to get more people on our side. We should all thank Michelle Duggar. She thinks that she&rsquo;s stabbing gay Americans in the front, but what she&rsquo;s really doing is bloodying herself.<\/p>\n<p><em>Brian Moylan is a writer and pop culture junkie who lives in New York. His work has appeared in Gawker, VICE, <\/em>New York <em>magazine, and a few other safe-for-work publications.<\/em><\/p><aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-ad\" data-name=\"rr-ad\"><div class=\"right-rail-ad\" id=\"right-rail-ad-3599721\"><\/div><\/aside><aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-share\" data-name=\"rr-share\"><span class=\"social-links\">\n    <a class=\"time-icons time-icons-mail social-link-mail\" href=\"mailto:?subject=Thank%20You%2C%20Duggars%2C%20Your%20Homophobia%20Is%20Really%20a%20Public%20Service%20%7C%20TIME&body=Thank%20You%2C%20Duggars%2C%20Your%20Homophobia%20Is%20Really%20a%20Public%20Service%0A%0AWhen%20gay%20marriage%20is%20passing%20in%20state%20after%20state%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20easy%20to%20forget%20that%20not%20everyone%20is%20on%20the%20bandwagon%0A%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3599721%2Fmichelle-duggar-homophobia-gay-rights%2F\" data-event=\"email\" title=\"Click to Email this article\"><\/a>\n    <a class=\"time-icons time-icons-fb social-link-fb popup\" href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/sharer\/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3599721%2Fmichelle-duggar-homophobia-gay-rights%2F\" data-event=\"fb-share\" title=\"Click to post this article to Facebook\"><\/a>\n    <a class=\"time-icons time-icons-tw social-link-tw popup\" href=\"#\" data-href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwp.me%2Fp5HMd-f6s1&text=Thank%20you%2C%20Duggars%2C%20your%20homophobia%20is%20really%20a%20public%20service&via=TIMEIdeas\" data-event=\"tweet\" title=\"Click to Tweet this article\"><\/a>\n    <a class=\"time-icons time-icons-linkedin social-link-linkedin popup\" href=\"http:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/shareArticle?mini=true&url=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3599721%2Fmichelle-duggar-homophobia-gay-rights%2F&title=Thank+You%2C+Duggars%2C+Your+Homophobia+Is+Really+a+Public+Service\" data-event=\"linkedin\" title=\"Click to post this article to LinkedIn\"><\/a>\n    <a href=\"#\" class=\"time-icons time-icons-comment toggle-comments\" data-lf-site-id=\"314099\" data-lf-article-id=\"3599721\" data-url=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3599721\/michelle-